1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:02,040
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:03,880
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:04,710 --> 00:00:06,410
(Final Episode)

4
00:00:06,610 --> 00:00:07,710
(We're Getting Married. Wedding Day)

5
00:00:08,850 --> 00:00:11,320
Hey, we're really in-laws now.

6
00:00:11,650 --> 00:00:13,490
That's right. We're in-laws.

7
00:00:15,990 --> 00:00:18,620
Father,
your speech today was wonderful.

8
00:00:20,090 --> 00:00:23,260
- Was I okay today?
- Yes, you did great.

9
00:00:24,460 --> 00:00:26,800
- Bride and groom were beautiful.
- Yes.

10
00:00:26,870 --> 00:00:27,870
Yes.

11
00:00:29,170 --> 00:00:30,400
Our Dolphin is pretty too.

12
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:35,240
That kid.
Just wait until we get home...

13
00:00:35,570 --> 00:00:37,080
- Father, let's go.
- Leaving already?

14
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:38,280
- Yes, let's just go.
- Father, are you okay?

15
00:00:38,340 --> 00:00:40,150
- Goodbye.
- Are you feeling all right, Father?

16
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:42,050
- Yes.
- Are you leaving first?

17
00:00:42,110 --> 00:00:43,880
- Yes, okay.
- Goodbye.

18
00:00:44,020 --> 00:00:46,650
- Goodbye.
- Thank you for all your hard work.

19
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:48,050
Are you feeling all right?

20
00:00:48,820 --> 00:00:50,050
Father, let's go.

21
00:00:53,790 --> 00:00:54,860
Father.

22
00:00:56,030 --> 00:00:57,260
- Father.
- Grandfather.

23
00:00:57,330 --> 00:00:58,330
Father-in-law.

24
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,000
- Sir.
- Grandfather.

25
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:01,900
- Father-in-law.
- Oh my gosh, what happened?

26
00:01:01,970 --> 00:01:03,970
- Hurry, make the call.
- Okay.

27
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:06,540
Yes, call 911. Sir, can you hear me?

28
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:09,340
- He seems to be unconscious.
- He's burning up.

29
00:01:09,470 --> 00:01:10,840
What? Wait.

30
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:13,480
We have to get him
to a hospital quickly.

31
00:01:28,390 --> 00:01:30,400
(Restricted Area)

32
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:31,830
(Hanguk University Hospital)

33
00:01:33,030 --> 00:01:35,670
Why didn't you tell me?

34
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:38,400
I'm sorry, Young Lady.

35
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:40,410
Father told me not to worry you...

36
00:01:40,470 --> 00:01:42,210
while you were getting ready
for the baby.

37
00:01:42,270 --> 00:01:43,640
He was very insistent.

38
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:46,140
Even so...

39
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:49,810
How could you keep it just from me?

40
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,450
It's because I knew
you'd react like this.

41
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:54,390
When Mom passed away,

42
00:01:55,090 --> 00:01:57,060
I saw how much you struggled.

43
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,190
That's why...

44
00:02:00,730 --> 00:02:03,660
What will I do
if something happens to Father too?

45
00:02:05,130 --> 00:02:06,130
Dong Suk.

46
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:07,830
Why would you say that?

47
00:02:08,570 --> 00:02:11,040
Father-in-law will pull through.
Don't worry.

48
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:14,740
Ji Hu, it's okay.

49
00:02:15,570 --> 00:02:17,280
It'll be fine. Don't worry.

50
00:02:21,650 --> 00:02:23,050
(Restricted Area)

51
00:02:24,450 --> 00:02:26,780
- Hyun Bin.
- What about Grandfather?

52
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:30,860
He's getting emergency treatment
in the ICU right now.

53
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,760
(Restricted Area)

54
00:02:40,230 --> 00:02:42,230
(Family Waiting Room)

55
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,240
What a relief.

56
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:51,210
Okay, right.

57
00:02:52,410 --> 00:02:53,480
How is he?

58
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:56,710
He got through the worst of it
with an emergency transfusion,

59
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:58,380
and his condition is stable.

60
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:02,850
But his inflammation levels
are high,

61
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:06,260
so they said we have
to monitor his progress.

62
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,630
Because he was receiving
chemotherapy,

63
00:03:08,690 --> 00:03:10,500
his immune system is
completely depleted,

64
00:03:10,930 --> 00:03:12,530
I think he's developed an infection.

65
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:18,200
Anyway, I'm worried that Dong Suk
must have been very shocked.

66
00:03:18,340 --> 00:03:19,400
I know.

67
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:25,340
What will you do now that...

68
00:03:25,410 --> 00:03:26,410
you've canceled
your whole honeymoon?

69
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:30,580
We'll go once Grandfather recovers.
Please don't worry about it.

70
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:33,990
Sister-in-law,
you would know, right?

71
00:03:34,220 --> 00:03:36,390
Is Grandfather really
going to be okay?

72
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:39,820
He has to be. And he will be.

73
00:03:40,330 --> 00:03:41,560
In that case, would it be okay...

74
00:03:41,630 --> 00:03:43,360
if I stayed at my mom's house
starting today?

75
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:44,930
Because you're worried
about your mom?

76
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:48,100
- Yes.
- I already cleaned out my old room.

77
00:03:48,230 --> 00:03:50,570
I'll help you move your things.

78
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:52,140
Thank you.

79
00:03:54,940 --> 00:03:56,240
Did you finish
cleaning Ju Ah's room?

80
00:03:56,310 --> 00:03:58,540
Yes. Because Hyun Bin
and Ji Hu said they are coming...

81
00:03:58,610 --> 00:04:00,110
- I'll go out and get them.
- Okay.

82
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:01,180
Yes.

83
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:05,820
- Dong Suk.
- Yes.

84
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:07,120
Can we talk for a minute?

85
00:04:07,950 --> 00:04:08,950
Yes.

86
00:04:15,290 --> 00:04:16,560
Are you feeling a bit better?

87
00:04:17,730 --> 00:04:20,400
Yes. Thank you, Father,

88
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:22,730
for taking care
of my father all this time.

89
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,000
Of course I had to.

90
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:28,370
That way, he'd take care of me
if I ever got sick.

91
00:04:29,610 --> 00:04:30,610
Yes.

92
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,710
I really wish he could.

93
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:38,020
Nothing's happening right
this instant, so don't cry.

94
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:39,320
Okay?

95
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:40,790
Yes, Father.

96
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:45,390
It made your father happy
to see you living a happy life.

97
00:04:45,890 --> 00:04:47,060
Just focus on having
a beautiful daughter...

98
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:48,130
who looks just like you.

99
00:04:48,730 --> 00:04:49,730
Stinky Dong Suk.

100
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Oh my, Father.

101
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:53,930
You always used to call me
"Stinky Dong Suk" to tease me.

102
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Do you remember?

103
00:04:55,570 --> 00:04:57,370
At your school entrance ceremony...

104
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:00,570
I made the handkerchief
you wore under your name tag.

105
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:02,640
Yes, that's right.

106
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,910
Whenever
you got scolded by your father...

107
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:06,240
and came outside crying...

108
00:05:06,380 --> 00:05:08,810
I'd take your hand
and we'd go to the corner store,

109
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:10,480
and I'd buy you hard candy. Right?

110
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:12,280
Yes.

111
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,690
Oh my.

112
00:05:14,450 --> 00:05:16,520
My goodness, to think
our little Stinky Dong Suk...

113
00:05:16,590 --> 00:05:17,790
became my daughter-in-law.

114
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:21,090
I always told you to marry my son
when you grew up.

115
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,660
Oh, my.

116
00:05:32,470 --> 00:05:35,270
You prepared quite a lot, Mother.

117
00:05:35,570 --> 00:05:36,570
You're right.

118
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:38,980
You decorated our newlywed room
completely to your taste.

119
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,950
What, you don't like it?

120
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:44,250
No, not at all. My taste is
exactly the same as yours.

121
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,850
Really? That's a relief.

122
00:05:49,890 --> 00:05:53,620
- Why?
- Could you please give us a moment?

123
00:05:54,330 --> 00:05:57,560
Oh, look at me.
Go on, do what you need to do.

124
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:03,530
I'm so tired. I think
we should tour the house tomorrow.

125
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,540
- Oh, right. Let's do that.
- Don't sit there.

126
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:09,870
What?

127
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:13,540
Go change and head to the hospital.
Your father is there all alone.

128
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:18,020
- How can I on our first night?
- Didn't you hear my grandfather?

129
00:06:18,950 --> 00:06:21,690
He told us not to cherish
only special days.

130
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:25,460
Still, I feel too sorry to do that.

131
00:06:26,390 --> 00:06:27,390
None of that.

132
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:30,230
Should a couple only be together
on good days?

133
00:06:30,660 --> 00:06:33,160
Besides, when my mom was sick,

134
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:35,330
I got through it thanks to you,
darling.

135
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:38,840
- Darling?
- Yes, darling.

136
00:06:39,370 --> 00:06:40,770
Why? Is it weird?

137
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:43,710
No, I just like it.

138
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:46,640
So hurry up and go, darling.

139
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:01,560
Hey, Dong Ik.

140
00:07:01,930 --> 00:07:04,230
Jeong Han, what are you doing here?

141
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:09,930
I came because I thought
my in-law might be lonely.

142
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:15,370
What?

143
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:17,740
Father-in-law, you were here too?

144
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,610
You don't even see your own father?

145
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:23,750
Here, change into these.
They're comfortable clothes.

146
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:28,450
But how did you get here?
Today's your wedding night.

147
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:32,560
Your daughter kept insisting that
I go, Father-in-law.

148
00:07:32,620 --> 00:07:34,960
Of course.
She takes after her mother.

149
00:07:35,030 --> 00:07:36,030
Goodness...

150
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,400
What are we going to do?

151
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:39,730
I'm so sorry you couldn't
even go on your honeymoon.

152
00:07:40,030 --> 00:07:41,370
Is today the only day we have?

153
00:07:41,900 --> 00:07:44,770
I'll do better from now on.
Don't worry, Father-in-law.

154
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,270
I asked, you know.

155
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:52,840
- Have a seat, son-in-law. Sit. Yes.
- Okay.

156
00:07:55,250 --> 00:07:56,380
Right.

157
00:07:57,820 --> 00:07:59,280
This is reassuring. Yes.

158
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:01,120
Thank you so much.

159
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:05,660
- He'll recover. Okay? Don't worry.
- Right.

160
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:22,840
- Good morning, Grandma.
- Good morning. Did you sleep well?

161
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:24,740
What about Father? Is he sleeping?

162
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:27,210
Oh, no, he said he was going
to take over for Jeong Han,

163
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,550
so he went to the hospital
at the crack of dawn.

164
00:08:28,610 --> 00:08:29,610
Jeong Han is sleeping.

165
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:31,480
Thank you so much.

166
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:36,220
Don't thank me.
We're all family. It's what we do.

167
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:39,090
After breakfast,
Dong Suk and I are planning to go.

168
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:40,560
Dong Suk didn't sleep well
last night,

169
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:41,560
so she's still sleeping.

170
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:42,830
I see.

171
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:45,300
You know,
I thought it would feel empty...

172
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,630
after sending Ju Ah off,

173
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,430
but having my grandson
here is really nice.

174
00:08:49,830 --> 00:08:51,740
Is this
the "happy soybean paste stew" smell...

175
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,970
- Grandfather talked about?
- What?

176
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,610
- Yes.
- Good morning.

177
00:08:56,940 --> 00:09:00,480
Oh my. Ji Hu, you're already up.
You're better than Ju Ah.

178
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:03,080
I wonder if she's even up yet.

179
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:05,920
Oh, she has a few days off.
She should be allowed to sleep in.

180
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:09,050
Still, should she be doing that
on her first day with the in-laws?

181
00:09:09,220 --> 00:09:11,820
Oh, don't worry about it.

182
00:09:11,890 --> 00:09:14,760
Right, she'll figure it out.
Honestly.

183
00:09:17,230 --> 00:09:18,830
Smells good.

184
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:23,330
- Young Lady.
- Hello...

185
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:25,440
Did you sleep well, Sister-in-law?

186
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,940
Did you not sleep well?

187
00:09:28,540 --> 00:09:30,140
Yes, I suppose so.

188
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:34,510
Grandfather is more stable now,
so no more worrying.

189
00:09:36,180 --> 00:09:39,220
But it was your wedding night
and you had to sleep alone?

190
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:41,690
Well, we have the rest
of our lives to be together.

191
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:45,990
But why are you speaking
so formally?

192
00:09:46,990 --> 00:09:50,230
Well, this is my in-laws' house,
and you are the Young Lady.

193
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:52,160
Oh, come on.
Let's be casual with each other.

194
00:09:52,230 --> 00:09:53,230
Okay?

195
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:54,800
Okay.

196
00:09:55,170 --> 00:09:58,070
But my being here isn't
making you uncomfortable, is it?

197
00:09:58,140 --> 00:10:01,770
Oh, not at all. I've always dreamed
of having a sister.

198
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:04,110
- Me too.
- Really?

199
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:05,180
Yes.

200
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:10,820
Then we can get matching pajamas
and stay up all night talking...

201
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:14,290
- A girls' night every weekend?
- Wow, I'd love that.

202
00:10:15,020 --> 00:10:16,520
Says who?

203
00:10:16,990 --> 00:10:19,390
Oh, you're back?
Were you at the hospital all night?

204
00:10:19,490 --> 00:10:21,990
Yes, I didn't get a wink of sleep.

205
00:10:22,530 --> 00:10:25,130
Our wedding night starts now.

206
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:29,370
- What are you doing? Oh my, wait...
- Allow me.

207
00:10:29,430 --> 00:10:31,140
What is with you right now?

208
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,640
Seriously,
first thing in the morning.

209
00:10:34,870 --> 00:10:37,840
My eyes.
I need to go wash out my eyes.

210
00:10:42,650 --> 00:10:44,950
Mother,
we're going to visit my parents...

211
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,020
after breakfast.

212
00:10:46,620 --> 00:10:47,620
Okay.

213
00:10:47,950 --> 00:10:50,090
You're supposed to go
greet your parents...

214
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:51,220
after the honeymoon...

215
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:54,390
How about at least taking a gift
with you?

216
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:59,600
- That's what I was thinking.
- Oh, really?

217
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:04,440
Oh my, Ju Ah, what are you doing?
What are you doing here?

218
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:06,840
What?
I've been doing this the whole time.

219
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:09,570
No, don't work. Don't do anything.

220
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:11,540
I promised my grandmother
that I wouldn't make you...

221
00:11:11,610 --> 00:11:13,410
suffer as a new bride.

222
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,280
How is this suffering?

223
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,620
It's only natural
that we prepare meals together.

224
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:20,480
What? Didn't you say you wanted
to leave the housework to me?

225
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:23,020
That was for when we both
have to go to work.

226
00:11:23,090 --> 00:11:24,660
Hey, that's enough.

227
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:27,260
Just go upstairs and rest,
Daughter-in-law.

228
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:29,060
Oh, Mother, how can I rest...

229
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:31,460
when you're acting like this
so early?

230
00:11:31,530 --> 00:11:35,630
Oh, don't feel pressured.
I really enjoy doing this.

231
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:40,040
Even if you enjoy doing it,
it's a burden to me.

232
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:42,940
Oh my, why would you feel burdened?

233
00:11:43,010 --> 00:11:45,580
This kitchen has always
been my responsibility.

234
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:48,950
Do you really think so?

235
00:11:49,210 --> 00:11:52,650
Think so? It's not a thought.
It's just the way it is.

236
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:58,890
Mother,
you're really a bit old-fashioned.

237
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:02,390
What? Old-fashioned?

238
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:07,730
Is this round one of Mother-in-law
versus Daughter-in-law?

239
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:10,970
Let them be. It's entertaining.

240
00:12:14,070 --> 00:12:16,540
Thinking the kitchen belongs
only to the woman of the house...

241
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:19,140
is a very outdated idea.

242
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:22,810
What are you talking about?

243
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:25,320
This system
where one person is responsible...

244
00:12:25,420 --> 00:12:27,490
for all the housework
is so inefficient.

245
00:12:27,550 --> 00:12:29,690
Goodness,
you do not talk about efficiency...

246
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:30,750
with family.

247
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:32,460
It is even more important
with family.

248
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:34,690
That is how you avoid
needless conflict.

249
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:37,290
From now on, the housework...

250
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:40,230
will be divided among us. All right?

251
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:43,630
What? What is with this girl?

252
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:46,870
The score is 1 to 0.

253
00:12:52,780 --> 00:12:56,910
How could you pretend you were away
on a trip like that, Father?

254
00:12:57,410 --> 00:13:00,180
I could have fooled you
all perfectly.

255
00:13:02,090 --> 00:13:03,320
How are you feeling?

256
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:07,590
Good. I feel much lighter.

257
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:11,200
You just came back from the dead
and you are acting tough.

258
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,800
Man, you scared us.

259
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:17,400
- Were you worried?
- You scared me to death.

260
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:24,280
Good grief.
How can you all be laughing?

261
00:13:29,780 --> 00:13:31,820
(Hanguk University Hospital)

262
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:34,190
Fortunately, he is responding well
to the antibiotics,

263
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:36,220
and his inflammation levels
are dropping quickly.

264
00:13:36,450 --> 00:13:39,560
Thank you.
Thank you so much, Doctor.

265
00:13:39,620 --> 00:13:42,560
So, will he continue chemotherapy
as before?

266
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:45,400
While Father still
has some strength,

267
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:48,830
we should do
the hematopoietic stem cell transplant.

268
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,230
A transplant?

269
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,870
But you said a transplant
is also dangerous.

270
00:13:52,940 --> 00:13:55,310
That is true.
However, in your father's case,

271
00:13:55,370 --> 00:13:56,510
a high risk of relapse...

272
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:58,710
has been confirmed
due to a gene mutation.

273
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:03,810
If the transplant is successful
and the graft takes,

274
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,450
we can hope for long-term survival.

275
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:08,550
So please,
discuss it as a family and decide.

276
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:10,750
Yes.

277
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:14,060
Forget it.

278
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:17,390
They said I might die
even with the transplant.

279
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:19,930
I would rather just make
the most of the time I have left.

280
00:14:21,070 --> 00:14:23,530
What if something goes wrong
with the transplant, Dong Ik?

281
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,540
Father-in-law,
if you become resistant...

282
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,670
to the chemotherapy and it relapses,

283
00:14:28,740 --> 00:14:30,740
they say there will be nothing left
they can do.

284
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:35,550
If it is a risk either way,
you have to try it. Right?

285
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:36,750
Hey.

286
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:39,580
How can you be so blunt
when it's not your problem?

287
00:14:39,650 --> 00:14:42,250
I am just trying to look
on the bright side.

288
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:45,690
If it goes well, you can see
Dong Ik become a city councilman...

289
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:49,260
and see Dong Suk have her baby.
Right?

290
00:14:49,330 --> 00:14:50,330
He's right.

291
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:59,470
So,
is Father getting the transplant?

292
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:02,640
Yes. Thankfully, he agreed.

293
00:15:02,810 --> 00:15:05,940
Then do you not need
a hematopoietic stem cell donor?

294
00:15:06,180 --> 00:15:08,350
Since Father's siblings
have all passed away,

295
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:12,280
among the registered donors,
they say we have to find a match.

296
00:15:12,580 --> 00:15:16,720
Anyone? Can anyone be a donor?
Then shouldn't I get tested?

297
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:19,060
- I will do it. Me.
- Well...

298
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:22,330
It turns out you cannot
because of the age limit.

299
00:15:23,060 --> 00:15:25,030
They say you can only register
as a potential donor...

300
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:26,130
until you are 40 years old.

301
00:15:27,730 --> 00:15:31,470
If we cannot find one,
between Dong Ik and me,

302
00:15:31,540 --> 00:15:33,970
they said it is possible to do
a half-matched transplant.

303
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,970
Half? They can do it
with only a half match?

304
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:39,480
Well, they said it is possible.

305
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:43,650
So my dad
and my aunt had their blood tested.

306
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:48,150
- It'll take a few days for results.
- What results?

307
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:51,190
Even as his children,
depending on the test results,

308
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:54,930
- they might not be able to donate.
- I see.

309
00:15:55,190 --> 00:15:56,790
Their tissue type
might not be compatible...

310
00:15:56,860 --> 00:15:59,600
or their health might not
be suitable for donation.

311
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:03,600
It would be best if a match is found
among the potential donors.

312
00:16:03,670 --> 00:16:04,670
Yes.

313
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:08,740
We might find a more suitable person
among the unrelated donors.

314
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:13,910
Right. Let us all be hopeful. Okay?

315
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,980
- Do not be too impatient.
- Yes.

316
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:20,450
Hey, why are you two still here?

317
00:16:20,850 --> 00:16:22,190
Hurry up and go home.

318
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:25,990
Dad, really, can I not even visit
my own parents' house freely?

319
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:28,030
Hurry up and go make dinner.

320
00:16:28,590 --> 00:16:29,590
I was going to.

321
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:35,800
Smells delicious.

322
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:39,140
You're home?
You haven't eaten dinner, right?

323
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,640
I made everything,
so go ahead and eat.

324
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:42,540
I'm going to take this lunch box
to the hospital.

325
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,110
Mother, stop.

326
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:45,740
Why?

327
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:48,410
- You go.
- I was going to anyway.

328
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,450
I wanted to go.

329
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:53,380
Mother, you've been doing chores
since this morning,

330
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,390
packed lunch boxes,
and for Uncle and Auntie...

331
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:59,120
No, you even packed food
for his aunt and uncle, right?

332
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:01,230
How did you know that?

333
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,960
We met them on our way here.

334
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:05,530
This is her family home, you know.

335
00:17:05,930 --> 00:17:08,470
She's trying to have a baby.
I just packed a few things for her.

336
00:17:08,530 --> 00:17:11,170
Anyway, Mother, you should rest now.

337
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:14,370
Yes, please rest.
I'll change, eat, and then go.

338
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:15,940
- Go.
- Okay.

339
00:17:18,010 --> 00:17:19,540
But I really do enjoy this...

340
00:17:23,010 --> 00:17:26,080
- What?
- Why is the room so clean?

341
00:17:27,050 --> 00:17:29,250
I know, right?
Mother must have cleaned all this.

342
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:31,460
Seriously? This isn't a hotel.

343
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:33,990
She even made the bed
with perfect corners.

344
00:17:34,860 --> 00:17:37,390
Wait, hold on.
Are you going to fight again?

345
00:17:37,630 --> 00:17:39,130
Fighting?
This is a coordination process...

346
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:41,500
for a healthy mother-in-law
and daughter-in-law relationship.

347
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:55,810
What is it?

348
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:03,390
Is this the long-awaited
round two...

349
00:18:03,450 --> 00:18:04,960
of Mother-in-law
versus Daughter-in-law?

350
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:08,760
No, it's already round three.

351
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:14,200
Mother, why did you clean our room?

352
00:18:15,370 --> 00:18:17,970
Well, I just went in to see
if there was any laundry,

353
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:20,240
and the room was so messy,
so I tidied up a bit.

354
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:21,810
Don't you remember...

355
00:18:21,870 --> 00:18:23,740
the In-Law Conflict
Prevention Agreement?

356
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:25,180
Article 3, Section 2 says...

357
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:27,380
Both parties shall mutually
respect each other's privacy.

358
00:18:28,780 --> 00:18:30,780
Come on,
how is laundry a matter of privacy?

359
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:34,050
From now on,
you're not allowed in our room...

360
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:35,890
without prior consent. Understood?

361
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:39,160
So I can't even go in?

362
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:42,690
Yes.
You must get our consent beforehand.

363
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:46,630
Mother?

364
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:50,330
Fine, I get it.

365
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:54,070
The score is 3 to 0.

366
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:56,070
A complete victory
for my sister-in-law.

367
00:18:56,370 --> 00:18:57,370
Hey.

368
00:19:00,310 --> 00:19:02,810
Yes. Father, I'm about to leave.

369
00:19:04,650 --> 00:19:05,650
What?

370
00:19:08,350 --> 00:19:10,920
Yes. I'll tell them. Yes.

371
00:19:11,620 --> 00:19:14,490
What? What is it?
Is something wrong with Grandfather?

372
00:19:14,790 --> 00:19:18,100
Among the currently
registered unrelated donors,

373
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,400
they said there's no one
who's a match for Grandfather.

374
00:19:21,330 --> 00:19:23,600
Then what's going to happen?

375
00:19:24,070 --> 00:19:27,240
Donors are continuously registered,
so we can wait a bit longer,

376
00:19:27,770 --> 00:19:30,410
or Father and Aunt
might be able to donate.

377
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:39,280
- It's not possible? For both of us?
- Yes, for both of you,

378
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:42,590
proceeding with the transplant
is too risky immunologically.

379
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:46,260
But what does that...

380
00:19:46,890 --> 00:19:48,690
It means your father's body
might not accept...

381
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:50,360
either
of your hematopoietic stem cells,

382
00:19:50,630 --> 00:19:52,730
or conversely,
the transplanted immune cells...

383
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,670
might attack your father's body.

384
00:19:57,500 --> 00:20:00,870
So, what should we do now, Doctor?

385
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,140
For now, we'll continue
with the chemotherapy...

386
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:05,610
and wait for a suitable person...

387
00:20:05,740 --> 00:20:08,010
to register as an unrelated donor.
We have to...

388
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:10,150
hang in there
and wait as long as we can.

389
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:13,980
What do we do?

390
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:18,320
That's a relief.

391
00:20:18,620 --> 00:20:21,760
I was worried I'd make
my kids suffer for no reason.

392
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:25,500
They said new people are always
registering, so let's wait.

393
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:30,670
Even if I wait,
my turn will never come.

394
00:20:31,170 --> 00:20:34,570
- Why are you so pessimistic?
- I'm being realistic.

395
00:20:35,470 --> 00:20:37,210
Still, I'm going to hold on to hope.

396
00:20:37,910 --> 00:20:41,350
Gong Gi Cheol,
I'm not a good person.

397
00:20:42,180 --> 00:20:45,220
But I'm blessed with good children
and good friends.

398
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,590
So what more could I ask for?

399
00:20:49,620 --> 00:20:51,050
That would be greedy.

400
00:20:54,220 --> 00:20:55,790
What's wrong with being greedy?

401
00:20:57,090 --> 00:20:59,230
Be greedy and take the blessing.

402
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:02,000
Then once you get healthy,
you can spend...

403
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:03,630
your life paying it back.

404
00:21:21,820 --> 00:21:23,690
On the bulletin boards
for the Merchants' Association...

405
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:24,760
and the Medical Association,

406
00:21:25,620 --> 00:21:28,890
I posted asking people
to register to donate.

407
00:21:30,190 --> 00:21:33,400
They said the odds
of finding a match...

408
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:35,070
are 1 in 20,000.

409
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:38,740
That means you'd need 20,000 donors,

410
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:41,240
just to find one person
who's a match for my father.

411
00:21:43,570 --> 00:21:45,880
Even in situations
that seem hopeless,

412
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:49,110
if the patient
and their family don't give up,

413
00:21:49,610 --> 00:21:51,950
a miracle will eventually happen.

414
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:54,180
Yes.

415
00:21:54,690 --> 00:21:57,820
Hey, let's pull ourselves together,
okay?

416
00:21:57,990 --> 00:22:00,320
Let's just focus on doing everything
we can right now.

417
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:01,990
Like what?

418
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:06,700
- What am I supposed to do?
- You need to get elected. Got it?

419
00:22:07,230 --> 00:22:09,030
Let's make your father's wish
come true. Okay?

420
00:22:09,770 --> 00:22:11,400
Do you think
he can hang on until then?

421
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:12,540
Of course. Hey,

422
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:14,270
you need to be strong first, man.
Okay?

423
00:22:48,110 --> 00:22:49,110
Mother.

424
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:54,910
Ju Ah, what am I going to do?

425
00:22:55,950 --> 00:22:57,350
What should I do?

426
00:22:58,950 --> 00:23:00,320
Mother.

427
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:04,650
I don't know
what I'm supposed to do.

428
00:23:05,490 --> 00:23:06,620
What do I do?

429
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,530
What do I do?

430
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,400
Is she still crying?

431
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:18,170
Yes. I'm so worried
because we start work tomorrow.

432
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,870
All right. I'll check in on her.

433
00:23:24,710 --> 00:23:26,010
I'm so sorry, Mother.

434
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:29,810
My mother doesn't have any friends
or anyone to turn to,

435
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:31,920
so I shamelessly
asked for your help.

436
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:33,750
I understand.

437
00:23:34,450 --> 00:23:36,920
You two get some rest.
Don't worry too much.

438
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:48,530
Oh, Dr. Han.

439
00:23:49,330 --> 00:23:50,800
What brings you here?

440
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:53,600
Let's have some tea.

441
00:23:56,070 --> 00:23:58,840
Oh no,
did I do something wrong again?

442
00:23:59,540 --> 00:24:00,810
What did Ju Ah say?

443
00:24:01,410 --> 00:24:05,150
- Well...
- I'm not giving her a hard time,

444
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,080
and I'm following
our agreement very well.

445
00:24:08,590 --> 00:24:09,620
Ju Ah says...

446
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:12,760
she's very worried about you.

447
00:24:15,260 --> 00:24:17,530
That's why I came.
I was worried too.

448
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:23,100
So are you here to give me
a therapy session?

449
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,300
No.

450
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:27,570
I just came to be a friend.

451
00:24:28,510 --> 00:24:29,970
It's give and take.

452
00:24:30,540 --> 00:24:33,210
Thanks to that surprise lecture
you arranged,

453
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:36,250
I got a lot of my confidence back.

454
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,450
I'm honored.

455
00:24:41,220 --> 00:24:44,390
For someone as famous
as you to offer to be my friend.

456
00:24:44,750 --> 00:24:46,760
I appreciate you saying that.

457
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:50,290
Though I'm not sure
how long I'll be famous.

458
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:51,960
Oh, don't say that.

459
00:24:52,130 --> 00:24:54,970
You're the most
famous person I know.

460
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:58,740
You need to get well soon
and make a comeback.

461
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:02,710
When you do, I'll be your manager.

462
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:07,780
I came here to comfort you,
but you're comforting me instead.

463
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:11,080
I wasn't trying to comfort you.

464
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:13,320
I truly believe it.

465
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:17,120
In that case...

466
00:25:17,890 --> 00:25:19,490
you should also believe...

467
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:22,330
that your father-in-law
will get better.

468
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:26,600
All right?

469
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:30,070
Yes.

470
00:25:32,870 --> 00:25:34,940
So we just have to wait for a donor?

471
00:25:35,710 --> 00:25:39,110
Yes. New people register every day.

472
00:25:39,610 --> 00:25:41,750
Well, among the new people
who register,

473
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:44,780
the chances of finding
a match are still slim.

474
00:25:48,450 --> 00:25:50,290
I wonder
if I can register to be a donor.

475
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:53,390
You can. They said anyone
under 40 is eligible,

476
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:54,990
so we just
registered on our way here.

477
00:25:55,890 --> 00:25:57,290
How do you do that?

478
00:25:57,530 --> 00:25:59,130
Just go to a Blood Donation Center,

479
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:01,770
apply to be a donor,
and give a blood sample. That's it.

480
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,970
That's simpler than I thought.

481
00:26:04,030 --> 00:26:06,500
I thought they'd take bone marrow
right away.

482
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:09,170
They only do that once
a registered donor is confirmed...

483
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,510
as the one to make the donation.

484
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:15,380
I mean, it might not be a huge help,
but should we do it too?

485
00:26:15,510 --> 00:26:19,480
- Wait. What are the odds again?
- The odds are 1 in 20,000.

486
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:26,960
Our company has
over 20,000 employees.

487
00:26:27,390 --> 00:26:29,390
Shall we try to up the odds, then?

488
00:26:30,060 --> 00:26:31,700
Should I post a notice
on the company message board...

489
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:32,860
encouraging people to participate?

490
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:35,030
He's so quick on the uptake.

491
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:39,900
- You'd really do that?
- Wow, thank you so much.

492
00:26:43,910 --> 00:26:44,910
We're counting on you.

493
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:48,910
Oh, of course.
I'll tell my son and grandson, too.

494
00:26:48,980 --> 00:26:51,250
Thank you, ma'am. Please do.
I'm counting on you.

495
00:26:52,180 --> 00:26:54,520
Oh Jin Ah, what are you doing?

496
00:26:55,550 --> 00:26:57,220
Asking family members
under 40 to register...

497
00:26:57,290 --> 00:26:58,690
as hematopoietic stem cell donors.

498
00:26:58,760 --> 00:27:03,330
- I'm encouraging them to do it.
- I see. I appreciate it, but...

499
00:27:03,930 --> 00:27:05,330
the odds are so slim.

500
00:27:05,630 --> 00:27:06,700
Why?

501
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,870
Does it seem like a drop
in the bucket to you?

502
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:11,070
You think it's useless, don't you?

503
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:13,900
No, that's not it. I just feel like
we're burdening them.

504
00:27:14,870 --> 00:27:17,110
Even if they can't
donate to Mr. Yang specifically,

505
00:27:17,170 --> 00:27:18,170
if they register,

506
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:20,440
they could still
save someone's life.

507
00:27:21,510 --> 00:27:23,780
Yes, that's true. Thank you.

508
00:27:24,980 --> 00:27:26,620
I also posted
on the police group chat...

509
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:28,620
and the alumni community page
to promote it.

510
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:29,850
Really?

511
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:33,020
Do you know how many police officers
there are in our country?

512
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,330
A whopping 130,000.

513
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:39,400
There are that many?

514
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:44,700
There are two million?

515
00:27:44,770 --> 00:27:47,640
Yoon Seo has
over two million followers?

516
00:27:47,770 --> 00:27:49,840
Yes. I'll talk to my sister...

517
00:27:49,910 --> 00:27:51,710
and suggest we start
a donation registration challenge.

518
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:54,340
She loves anything
that improves her public image.

519
00:27:55,110 --> 00:27:56,150
Really?

520
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,010
I felt bad
about what happened last time,

521
00:27:58,310 --> 00:27:59,780
so I wanted to make it up to you...

522
00:28:01,250 --> 00:28:02,920
Thank you so much.

523
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:05,090
Do I just have to go
to a Blood Donation Center?

524
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:08,020
Yes, I just went,
and it's simpler than you'd think.

525
00:28:09,460 --> 00:28:11,330
Then I'll talk
to the actors at our agency...

526
00:28:11,390 --> 00:28:12,600
and ask them to promote it.

527
00:28:14,030 --> 00:28:17,200
Thank you so much.
I really mean it. Thank you.

528
00:28:17,730 --> 00:28:19,900
(Hematopoietic Stem Cell
Donor Registration Form)

529
00:28:19,970 --> 00:28:21,910
The energizing force
of Onjeong Market.

530
00:28:21,970 --> 00:28:25,110
I'm independent candidate number five,
Yang Dong Ik.

531
00:28:25,180 --> 00:28:27,740
Now, with sincere leadership,

532
00:28:27,810 --> 00:28:29,450
I will breathe new life...

533
00:28:29,450 --> 00:28:31,550
- into this stagnant market.
- Into this stagnant market.

534
00:28:31,610 --> 00:28:34,180
Everyone,
he's a tireless public servant.

535
00:28:34,250 --> 00:28:36,990
Please be sure to vote for
candidate number five,

536
00:28:37,050 --> 00:28:38,050
Yang Dong Ik.

537
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:40,690
- We ask for your support.
- Candidate Yang.

538
00:28:40,820 --> 00:28:41,960
Thank you for your hard work.

539
00:28:42,630 --> 00:28:44,960
Mr. Yoon, thank you for coming.

540
00:28:45,030 --> 00:28:47,460
Having young merchants
like you here...

541
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,070
gives me a huge boost of energy.

542
00:28:50,300 --> 00:28:51,600
Ta-da.

543
00:28:52,370 --> 00:28:54,000
Oh my. Look.

544
00:28:55,070 --> 00:28:58,140
They said they'd help us,
so I sent them T-shirts in advance.

545
00:28:59,110 --> 00:29:01,640
But Mr. Yoon,
you arrived later than I thought.

546
00:29:01,810 --> 00:29:04,750
I had to go to the Blood Donation Center
to register as a donor.

547
00:29:05,180 --> 00:29:08,920
You never know. Any of us might be
the 1-in-20,000 winner.

548
00:29:09,490 --> 00:29:12,990
Of course. It's possible. Thank you.

549
00:29:13,190 --> 00:29:16,060
And also, I promoted it a lot
on online communities...

550
00:29:16,130 --> 00:29:17,530
for self-employed people.

551
00:29:17,590 --> 00:29:20,160
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

552
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:23,130
- Thank you so much.
- Oh, come on.

553
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:25,140
- Go, Yang Dong Ik. Go.
- Go.

554
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:28,440
- Go. Go.
- We'll support you all the way.

555
00:29:28,510 --> 00:29:31,110
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Yang Dong Ik is the best.

556
00:29:31,170 --> 00:29:33,840
- The best.
- Yang Dong Ik.

557
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:35,710
- Yang Dong Ik.
- Yang Dong Ik.

558
00:29:35,780 --> 00:29:38,480
- Yang Dong Ik.
- Yang Dong Ik.

559
00:29:43,090 --> 00:29:44,490
Studying?

560
00:29:45,490 --> 00:29:47,320
Going back to being a doctor?

561
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:50,990
Hey, how can I focus
on studying when you're this sick?

562
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:53,960
Then what are you doing?

563
00:29:57,430 --> 00:30:01,000
Seon Hae wrote me letters
for 30 years.

564
00:30:01,770 --> 00:30:04,010
I'm writing back to her.

565
00:30:05,580 --> 00:30:07,780
So lovey-dovey in your old age.

566
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:09,880
I'm jealous.

567
00:30:11,380 --> 00:30:15,550
If you're jealous, you lose.
You should get better soon,

568
00:30:16,020 --> 00:30:17,490
and get a girlfriend.

569
00:30:20,290 --> 00:30:21,720
Oh, he likes that.

570
00:30:24,530 --> 00:30:27,030
I'm worried that
they still haven't found a matching donor.

571
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:28,570
What?

572
00:30:28,570 --> 00:30:31,730
Well, the odds are very slim.

573
00:30:32,970 --> 00:30:35,810
What is it? You look like
you have something to tell me.

574
00:30:39,140 --> 00:30:42,050
Well, at the Onjeong Police Station,

575
00:30:42,110 --> 00:30:44,580
there's an opening
in the detective division,

576
00:30:45,250 --> 00:30:46,880
and Detective Jang recommended me.

577
00:30:47,380 --> 00:30:50,720
- The detective division?
- Yes. After we worked together,

578
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:52,390
I guess I made
a good impression on him.

579
00:30:54,660 --> 00:30:57,960
But you said you didn't want to date
because you were afraid of dying.

580
00:30:58,490 --> 00:31:00,860
The detective division,
isn't that really dangerous work?

581
00:31:01,060 --> 00:31:02,400
That's why I'm asking you.

582
00:31:02,470 --> 00:31:04,500
If you don't want me to,
I won't do it.

583
00:31:08,670 --> 00:31:09,910
Do you want to do it?

584
00:31:14,010 --> 00:31:17,150
If I get the chance,
I'd like to try.

585
00:31:17,850 --> 00:31:21,020
It's also the path my father
never got to finish.

586
00:31:23,990 --> 00:31:26,190
If you put it that way,
how can I stop you?

587
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:28,830
I guess you can't.

588
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:36,170
- Can I have some time to think?
- About what? Detective division?

589
00:31:37,770 --> 00:31:39,200
About us getting married.

590
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:45,740
(Not Pregnant)

591
00:31:52,580 --> 00:31:53,620
One line?

592
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:55,290
Yes.

593
00:31:58,120 --> 00:32:01,660
It's our first try, so it's okay.
We'll just try again next month.

594
00:32:03,390 --> 00:32:04,490
Honey...

595
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:07,000
Let's go to a clinic and try IVF.

596
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:10,500
Well, I don't want to do that.

597
00:32:10,930 --> 00:32:11,930
Why?

598
00:32:12,300 --> 00:32:13,400
You'd have to get shots,

599
00:32:13,470 --> 00:32:15,200
and I heard there are a lot
of side effects.

600
00:32:15,740 --> 00:32:19,040
- It'll be too hard on you.
- I don't mind if it's hard for me.

601
00:32:19,510 --> 00:32:22,010
How could it be harder
than what my father's going through?

602
00:32:22,410 --> 00:32:25,280
- Dong Suk.
- I don't care if it's hard.

603
00:32:26,580 --> 00:32:29,050
I'll do anything if it means
I can have a baby soon.

604
00:32:29,190 --> 00:32:30,390
It'll be even harder to conceive...

605
00:32:30,490 --> 00:32:32,020
if you're so impatient
and stressed out.

606
00:32:32,220 --> 00:32:34,790
Dong Suk, let's just
let it happen naturally, okay?

607
00:32:34,860 --> 00:32:37,160
We're running out of time.

608
00:32:39,060 --> 00:32:41,360
We have to have a baby
as soon as possible,

609
00:32:42,100 --> 00:32:43,730
because I think
it will give my father...

610
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:48,140
the will to fight.
So he can live a little longer.

611
00:32:48,840 --> 00:32:49,840
Okay, okay.

612
00:32:51,110 --> 00:32:53,280
I know exactly how you feel. But...

613
00:32:53,410 --> 00:32:57,280
I don't want to go to these lengths.
And you being like this?

614
00:32:57,350 --> 00:32:59,320
Your father wouldn't
want this either. Right?

615
00:32:59,650 --> 00:33:01,350
How would you know that?

616
00:33:02,690 --> 00:33:03,750
Dong Suk, please listen to me.

617
00:33:04,290 --> 00:33:05,920
Just listen to me.

618
00:33:05,990 --> 00:33:09,390
So should we do nothing
and just wait for my father to die?

619
00:33:09,460 --> 00:33:10,960
I'm not saying we do nothing...

620
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:12,060
Then, like that...

621
00:33:15,030 --> 00:33:17,870
Hey, what's going on here?

622
00:33:18,670 --> 00:33:19,870
I'm sorry.

623
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:22,570
I'm sorry, Mother.

624
00:33:23,740 --> 00:33:27,740
It's just that there's nothing
I can do for my father...

625
00:33:29,610 --> 00:33:30,780
Dong Suk.

626
00:33:31,250 --> 00:33:34,750
Why do you think your father
told you to have a baby?

627
00:33:36,820 --> 00:33:37,820
Do you think...

628
00:33:37,890 --> 00:33:39,320
it was because he wanted
to see a grandchild?

629
00:33:39,820 --> 00:33:41,090
No.

630
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:45,460
He just wanted to see you happy,
Dong Suk.

631
00:33:46,300 --> 00:33:47,760
I know...

632
00:33:48,100 --> 00:33:49,530
I know...

633
00:33:51,030 --> 00:33:52,370
Oh, goodness.

634
00:33:58,940 --> 00:34:00,180
Don't cry.

635
00:34:02,110 --> 00:34:03,480
Oh, dear.

636
00:34:06,950 --> 00:34:08,650
That's enough. Enough.

637
00:34:14,460 --> 00:34:16,990
Should we say a prayer on our walk?

638
00:34:18,860 --> 00:34:20,300
Are you that worried?

639
00:34:20,660 --> 00:34:21,660
No, it's just that...

640
00:34:21,730 --> 00:34:23,770
while I was writing a reply
in the diary,

641
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:27,470
Seon Chul's breathing was getting
more and more labored.

642
00:34:29,470 --> 00:34:31,270
You feel so helpless.

643
00:34:32,110 --> 00:34:34,580
That's why I thought
maybe we could pray.

644
00:34:35,140 --> 00:34:38,950
When a man who has been wronged
for 30 years prays,

645
00:34:39,580 --> 00:34:42,120
you would think someone would have
the decency to listen,

646
00:34:42,190 --> 00:34:43,190
would you not?

647
00:34:46,560 --> 00:34:47,790
Oh, Jeong Han.

648
00:34:48,490 --> 00:34:50,490
Yes, I was about to go hiking
with your father.

649
00:34:52,460 --> 00:34:53,460
What did you say?

650
00:34:54,230 --> 00:34:56,170
Oh, my gosh, are you serious?

651
00:34:57,500 --> 00:35:01,240
Oh, my goodness. They found a donor.

652
00:35:01,770 --> 00:35:05,440
Oh, dear. Oh, my goodness.
Thank you.

653
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:10,310
Thank you. Okay, yes.
All right, I got it.

654
00:35:13,420 --> 00:35:14,850
Well, if I had known my wish...

655
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:16,820
would be granted
just by saying it...

656
00:35:17,190 --> 00:35:20,020
maybe I should have complained
to the heavens a lot sooner.

657
00:35:22,690 --> 00:35:23,730
Wow.

658
00:35:24,890 --> 00:35:25,930
Just wow.

659
00:35:26,830 --> 00:35:28,230
Father.

660
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:31,130
The merchants
from the market sent a video...

661
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:33,340
to wish you a successful transplant.

662
00:35:34,070 --> 00:35:38,110
Mr. Yang.
You have to come back to us healthy.

663
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:42,310
The market feels so empty
without you yelling at us.

664
00:35:42,780 --> 00:35:45,450
We're waiting for you,
so get well soon.

665
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:47,320
- You can do it, Mr. Yang.
- You can do it, Mr. Yang.

666
00:35:47,680 --> 00:35:49,690
- Stay strong.
- Get well soon.

667
00:35:49,750 --> 00:35:51,920
- Get well, Mr. Yang.
- Thank you.

668
00:35:53,390 --> 00:35:54,390
Father-in-law.

669
00:35:54,690 --> 00:35:56,930
The sterile room might feel
a bit confining.

670
00:35:57,330 --> 00:35:59,530
But you need to trust
the medical staff...

671
00:35:59,630 --> 00:36:01,130
and be patient, understand?

672
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:03,600
Yes.

673
00:36:04,930 --> 00:36:05,940
Father.

674
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:08,370
You'll get through this, right?

675
00:36:10,340 --> 00:36:11,840
Put up a good fight, Grandfather.

676
00:36:12,210 --> 00:36:13,410
Grandfather,
you only ever fight battles...

677
00:36:13,480 --> 00:36:14,480
you know you'll win, right?

678
00:36:14,910 --> 00:36:17,110
Right. Don't worry.

679
00:36:18,310 --> 00:36:19,380
I'll tell myself...

680
00:36:19,950 --> 00:36:22,750
you're going on a trip, Father.

681
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:26,190
We'll hold down the fort
while you're gone.

682
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:30,060
Grandfather, don't you ever think
you're alone, okay?

683
00:36:30,690 --> 00:36:32,960
We'll be cheering for you.

684
00:37:02,290 --> 00:37:06,360
(Sterile Room)

685
00:37:22,550 --> 00:37:24,450
Look after the kids.

686
00:37:25,080 --> 00:37:27,180
None of that weak talk.

687
00:37:27,720 --> 00:37:30,120
Make sure you come back alive,
you hear?

688
00:37:31,850 --> 00:37:33,620
I'll be back.

689
00:37:35,790 --> 00:37:38,260
My goodness,
someone's been watching movies.

690
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:46,870
(Restricted Area)

691
00:37:55,510 --> 00:37:58,280
(Sterile Room)

692
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:14,900
Oh, look.

693
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,830
(2 Years Later)

694
00:38:16,930 --> 00:38:17,970
Ji Ah.

695
00:38:18,470 --> 00:38:20,270
That's it. You're walking so well.

696
00:38:20,570 --> 00:38:22,200
Ji Ah, over here.

697
00:38:22,270 --> 00:38:24,010
Ji Ah's walking. Oh, my gosh.

698
00:38:24,070 --> 00:38:26,580
She's walking so well.
I can't believe it.

699
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,510
There we go, there we go.

700
00:38:29,050 --> 00:38:30,410
Our Ji Ah did so well.

701
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:34,480
Hold on.
Hey, what's taking him so long?

702
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:37,650
Ji Ah. Oh my.

703
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:40,760
I'm sorry I'm late. I'm sorry.

704
00:38:40,820 --> 00:38:43,260
- What took you so long?
- Hey, Ji Ah.

705
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:46,060
Oh, goodness.
Thank you so much for your help...

706
00:38:46,130 --> 00:38:47,130
while you were busy.

707
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:50,130
- You should get going.
- I just changed her diaper.

708
00:38:50,130 --> 00:38:51,430
We're low on wipes.

709
00:38:51,770 --> 00:38:53,670
- Okay.
- We'll get going.

710
00:38:53,740 --> 00:38:56,840
Let's go.

711
00:38:56,910 --> 00:38:59,880
- Ji Ah, we're leaving now.
- Bye.

712
00:39:00,110 --> 00:39:02,550
- See you later.
- Bye.

713
00:39:02,610 --> 00:39:04,380
- Oh my.
- So cute.

714
00:39:04,980 --> 00:39:06,750
- See you.
- Look, she's saying bye.

715
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:08,120
Say bye.

716
00:39:08,950 --> 00:39:09,950
Bye-bye.

717
00:39:10,890 --> 00:39:12,560
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

718
00:39:12,620 --> 00:39:15,660
(Damga Charcoal Grill
Branch Two Grand Opening)

719
00:39:16,260 --> 00:39:17,790
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.

720
00:39:17,860 --> 00:39:19,100
- Yes.
- Here you go.

721
00:39:20,030 --> 00:39:21,130
Have a seat.

722
00:39:21,930 --> 00:39:23,900
Here are the pork ribs you ordered.

723
00:39:24,130 --> 00:39:25,130
The ribs are delicious.

724
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:26,870
Ma'am,
this must be a really popular spot.

725
00:39:26,940 --> 00:39:29,470
Oh? This is our second location.

726
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:33,510
It's packed with customers,
and everyone's so busy, right?

727
00:39:35,210 --> 00:39:36,780
Ji Ah, look. There's Mommy.

728
00:39:39,480 --> 00:39:42,020
- My Ji Ah is here.
- Mommy, Mommy.

729
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:44,020
Hey, wash your hands
before you touch her.

730
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:46,060
Oh my, my sweet Ji Ah is here.

731
00:39:46,120 --> 00:39:50,590
Oh, my goodness.
Daddy missed you so much,

732
00:39:50,660 --> 00:39:52,660
I could barely stand it.

733
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:56,070
But why did you bring Ji Ah?

734
00:39:56,130 --> 00:39:58,370
I thought Ju Ah was supposed
to watch her this weekend.

735
00:39:58,500 --> 00:40:00,240
Something came up suddenly
at Ju Ah's work,

736
00:40:00,300 --> 00:40:01,340
so she asked me to switch.

737
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:04,870
Auntie, congratulations
on opening your second location.

738
00:40:05,340 --> 00:40:07,010
Thanks. Go get something to eat.

739
00:40:07,410 --> 00:40:08,410
That's right, eat up.

740
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:09,680
You need to eat well
if you're going to work.

741
00:40:09,810 --> 00:40:12,450
You're just itching to put me
to work, aren't you?

742
00:40:12,780 --> 00:40:15,890
Hey, you brat. I raised you kids.
Can't you do this much for me?

743
00:40:16,450 --> 00:40:17,850
Yes, sir.

744
00:40:19,660 --> 00:40:22,690
- Oh, honestly. Stop it. Honestly.
- She's so pretty.

745
00:40:23,660 --> 00:40:27,330
Oh my, it's so crowded in here.
Hey, Ji Ah.

746
00:40:27,860 --> 00:40:29,130
Hello.

747
00:40:29,570 --> 00:40:31,870
Business is booming, isn't it?

748
00:40:32,100 --> 00:40:33,100
She's our lucky charm.

749
00:40:33,170 --> 00:40:34,340
Ji Ah must be
our little good luck charm.

750
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:36,040
That must be why business
is doing so well, right?

751
00:40:36,510 --> 00:40:37,510
I suppose so.

752
00:40:38,270 --> 00:40:40,640
Father would have been so happy
if he had seen this...

753
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:45,310
Mom, where's Dad?
Oh, is he not coming?

754
00:40:45,450 --> 00:40:49,390
Yes, you know he's even busier
on the weekends. Our Councilor Yang.

755
00:40:50,550 --> 00:40:51,550
(Prepay at Local Restaurants,
Revisit)

756
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:57,760
- No, no.
- Goodness.

757
00:40:57,830 --> 00:40:59,600
Well, look who it is.
Councilor Yang is here.

758
00:41:00,330 --> 00:41:01,730
Chief, thank you for your hard work.

759
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:03,300
You're here, Councilor Yang.

760
00:41:03,370 --> 00:41:04,700
There's a dangerous situation
at Onjeong Market.

761
00:41:04,770 --> 00:41:07,000
- Of course I had to come.
- Thank you.

762
00:41:12,110 --> 00:41:13,180
Hello. Yes.

763
00:41:14,610 --> 00:41:17,810
Yes. You're Manager Choi
from the city road division, right?

764
00:41:18,310 --> 00:41:20,820
This is Councilor Yang Dong Ik. Yes.

765
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:22,950
I've been telling you
since this morning that...

766
00:41:23,020 --> 00:41:25,050
there are signs of ground subsidence
at Onjeong Market,

767
00:41:25,390 --> 00:41:27,460
so why haven't you sent
a repair team yet?

768
00:41:27,860 --> 00:41:30,390
Don't you know that if it rains,
the whole thing could collapse?

769
00:41:30,660 --> 00:41:34,600
Will City Hall take responsibility
if there's an accident?

770
00:41:34,660 --> 00:41:35,730
Please take care of it.

771
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:37,100
Councilor Yang.

772
00:41:38,130 --> 00:41:39,900
Councilor Yang,
please take a good look into this.

773
00:41:39,970 --> 00:41:41,540
- Don't worry.
- Thank you.

774
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:44,310
- Everything will be fine.
- Yes, Councilor Yang is the best.

775
00:41:44,610 --> 00:41:45,610
Thank you.

776
00:41:51,310 --> 00:41:52,680
(A Free Checkup And Consultation)

777
00:41:52,750 --> 00:41:53,950
(Free Medical Service
For Local Residents)

778
00:41:54,050 --> 00:41:57,120
Hello, ma'am. Please stand here.

779
00:41:57,320 --> 00:42:01,490
Please take a look at this
and wait for a moment, okay?

780
00:42:01,560 --> 00:42:03,960
Ouch, that hurts, doesn't it?
Yes, yes.

781
00:42:04,460 --> 00:42:06,730
It hurts even when I do this.
Oh, dear.

782
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:08,030
- This is a little...
- Here. Right here.

783
00:42:08,100 --> 00:42:10,170
- They say I'm terribly ill...
- Do you take any vitamins?

784
00:42:10,230 --> 00:42:13,140
It's a throbbing pain, right?
Yes, I see. Oh, dear.

785
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:15,640
(Medication Counseling)

786
00:42:15,700 --> 00:42:20,140
Take it once in the morning
and once in the evening.

787
00:42:20,210 --> 00:42:22,180
You mentioned
it was about your child.

788
00:42:22,610 --> 00:42:25,280
So, what exactly is
the health problem?

789
00:42:28,650 --> 00:42:30,890
- You're home?
- Where's Ji Ah?

790
00:42:31,020 --> 00:42:32,290
Father, please be quiet.

791
00:42:32,590 --> 00:42:34,890
She just fell asleep.
She must have been tired...

792
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:36,390
because she's completely out.

793
00:42:37,390 --> 00:42:38,530
Dong Suk.

794
00:42:38,790 --> 00:42:40,400
I'm sorry I couldn't make it
to the grand opening...

795
00:42:40,460 --> 00:42:41,460
of your second store today.

796
00:42:41,530 --> 00:42:45,070
It's something you do every week.
You shouldn't skip it for me.

797
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:48,000
By the way, Dae Han,
are you really not going...

798
00:42:48,070 --> 00:42:49,770
to have a first birthday party
for Ji Ah?

799
00:42:49,910 --> 00:42:51,040
Well...

800
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:54,810
Let's just hand out some rice cakes
and take a family photo.

801
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:56,580
Especially
since my father-in-law isn't here.

802
00:42:57,580 --> 00:42:58,810
It doesn't feel right
to have a party.

803
00:42:59,580 --> 00:43:00,580
Oh, you're right.

804
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:04,250
I'm sure he believes that
you're all living well.

805
00:43:05,190 --> 00:43:08,120
- All right, let's get some rest.
- Okay.

806
00:43:08,190 --> 00:43:09,190
- Okay.
- Good night.

807
00:43:09,260 --> 00:43:10,990
- Get some rest, Mom.
- Okay.

808
00:43:33,920 --> 00:43:35,380
Wait a minute.

809
00:43:38,390 --> 00:43:39,390
Oh my.

810
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:42,590
You're up?
Aren't you two going to work today?

811
00:43:42,930 --> 00:43:44,260
Honey. Hyun Bin.

812
00:43:44,330 --> 00:43:46,200
Yang Hyun Bin. Hey, wake up.

813
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:47,930
What? What's going on?

814
00:43:48,060 --> 00:43:50,900
We're late.
Why didn't the alarm go off?

815
00:43:51,030 --> 00:43:52,500
Oh no.

816
00:43:52,570 --> 00:43:53,970
Hold on,
what was I going to wear today?

817
00:43:54,040 --> 00:43:56,470
Oh, right.
I forgot to do the laundry again.

818
00:43:57,270 --> 00:43:59,880
Sorry.
I meant to do it, but I forgot.

819
00:44:01,580 --> 00:44:02,640
What should I do?

820
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:05,280
- What? What?
- What is it?

821
00:44:05,750 --> 00:44:06,750
Are these our clothes?

822
00:44:07,120 --> 00:44:09,790
It looks like your mom
did our laundry and even ironed it.

823
00:44:09,850 --> 00:44:12,090
What? Did she come into our room
without asking again?

824
00:44:12,220 --> 00:44:13,590
Come on, there can be exceptions.

825
00:44:14,590 --> 00:44:17,860
Mother-in-law, you're my angel.
Thank you.

826
00:44:26,340 --> 00:44:27,600
You are welcome.

827
00:44:31,940 --> 00:44:33,140
- We're off.
- We're off.

828
00:44:33,210 --> 00:44:37,010
Hey, wait. Eat this before you go.

829
00:44:37,350 --> 00:44:38,350
You too, Hyun Bin.

830
00:44:38,980 --> 00:44:40,980
Gosh, I tell you to wake up
ten minutes earlier,

831
00:44:41,050 --> 00:44:42,480
but you always rush out like this.

832
00:44:42,890 --> 00:44:45,050
It's because those ten minutes
are the sweetest.

833
00:44:45,150 --> 00:44:46,790
This is what's really sweet.

834
00:44:47,090 --> 00:44:48,620
Why don't you two just move out?

835
00:44:48,620 --> 00:44:51,360
Live closer to work
so you can sleep in.

836
00:44:51,960 --> 00:44:53,530
Ju Ah absolutely refuses.

837
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:55,900
Here, Ju Ah, have one more.
You too, Hyun Bin.

838
00:44:56,070 --> 00:44:58,230
I'm going to live with you forever,
Mother.

839
00:44:58,530 --> 00:45:00,870
Says who?

840
00:45:01,770 --> 00:45:04,870
Mother, thank you.
I love you. I'm off.

841
00:45:08,640 --> 00:45:09,750
Honestly.

842
00:45:10,610 --> 00:45:11,650
They should have eaten more.

843
00:45:24,260 --> 00:45:26,100
Father, Mother.

844
00:45:27,400 --> 00:45:28,530
Our Ji Ah...

845
00:45:29,870 --> 00:45:32,170
She was teething all night,
so I didn't get a wink of sleep.

846
00:45:32,530 --> 00:45:34,440
So please,
can we skip the waltz today?

847
00:45:34,500 --> 00:45:35,700
Please. I'm begging you.

848
00:45:36,070 --> 00:45:37,210
All right, I get it.

849
00:45:40,510 --> 00:45:41,510
Please.

850
00:45:43,850 --> 00:45:47,420
- That kid, honestly...
- How can he be so...

851
00:45:47,620 --> 00:45:51,650
Isn't it exhausting doing treatments
three times a week?

852
00:45:52,050 --> 00:45:53,390
It's fine. I should do it more...

853
00:45:53,490 --> 00:45:55,120
so the number
of patients keeps growing.

854
00:45:55,390 --> 00:45:57,830
That's Han Seong Mi for you.

855
00:45:58,530 --> 00:46:01,130
But you know what day it is today,
right?

856
00:46:01,360 --> 00:46:03,200
I know, but I have
a Merchants' Association...

857
00:46:03,270 --> 00:46:04,270
meeting today.

858
00:46:04,630 --> 00:46:06,170
Isn't that a meeting
you have all the time?

859
00:46:06,740 --> 00:46:08,640
Can't you skip it for one day?

860
00:46:08,870 --> 00:46:11,110
I'm sorry.
I really want to go, but...

861
00:46:11,310 --> 00:46:15,140
you know how Bucket is these days.
He's been so difficult.

862
00:46:16,410 --> 00:46:18,650
I really don't know how
he changed so much.

863
00:46:18,710 --> 00:46:21,650
- It's ridiculous.
- I know, right? Gosh.

864
00:46:22,320 --> 00:46:23,890
How do I look?
Do I look handsome today?

865
00:46:24,350 --> 00:46:27,260
You do. But you're supposed
to be moderately handsome.

866
00:46:27,720 --> 00:46:31,090
Right. At this rate, I'm worried
all the women will fall for me.

867
00:46:31,390 --> 00:46:33,800
As if. Not while I'm around.

868
00:46:34,300 --> 00:46:37,700
That's true. Who would dare
compete with my Seon Hae? Right?

869
00:46:39,800 --> 00:46:41,700
Oh, you're out here.

870
00:46:42,400 --> 00:46:45,010
You two look so great today.

871
00:46:46,510 --> 00:46:48,740
Father, are you all ready for today?

872
00:46:49,040 --> 00:46:50,480
What's there to prepare?

873
00:46:50,750 --> 00:46:52,610
Don't say that.
You didn't sleep a wink...

874
00:46:52,680 --> 00:46:54,050
because you were so nervous.

875
00:46:54,950 --> 00:46:56,250
You'll do great.

876
00:46:56,850 --> 00:46:59,190
You do well today too.

877
00:46:59,390 --> 00:47:02,590
Yes.
But I'm a little nervous today too.

878
00:47:03,130 --> 00:47:04,260
Oh, the kids must be waiting.

879
00:47:04,330 --> 00:47:07,460
I'll get going first.
Okay, see you all later.

880
00:47:08,830 --> 00:47:09,930
Wow, Father. You look great.

881
00:47:10,930 --> 00:47:13,770
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

882
00:47:13,840 --> 00:47:15,740
Oh dear,
if it's spread to your fingertips,

883
00:47:15,800 --> 00:47:16,910
it must have hurt a lot.

884
00:47:17,070 --> 00:47:20,510
See? That's why I told you
to wear gloves when you cook.

885
00:47:20,980 --> 00:47:25,280
Oh, I had a sudden rush of customers
and I forgot.

886
00:47:25,350 --> 00:47:26,920
Excuses, excuses.

887
00:47:27,020 --> 00:47:30,620
Now, don't you dare
pop this blister on purpose.

888
00:47:30,690 --> 00:47:32,550
Yes, and be careful
not to get it wet,

889
00:47:32,620 --> 00:47:35,860
- so it doesn't get infected.
- If it swells up or starts to ooze,

890
00:47:35,920 --> 00:47:38,330
don't just put up with it.
Come right back. Okay?

891
00:47:39,260 --> 00:47:41,230
All right, I get it.

892
00:47:41,660 --> 00:47:45,070
Being nagged by two people
at once is exhausting.

893
00:47:46,440 --> 00:47:48,670
- Okay, take care. Yes.
- Okay.

894
00:47:50,370 --> 00:47:53,840
- Father, you should take a break.
- Should I?

895
00:47:53,910 --> 00:47:54,910
Yes.

896
00:47:56,910 --> 00:48:01,050
Goodness. Like father, like son.
They're so alike.

897
00:48:02,480 --> 00:48:05,620
Dr. Gong and I are only working
the morning shift today.

898
00:48:06,120 --> 00:48:07,720
Okay.

899
00:48:08,660 --> 00:48:12,260
Those two are always joined
at the hip. I'm so envious.

900
00:48:13,400 --> 00:48:15,200
I'm so lonely.

901
00:48:17,670 --> 00:48:20,770
(The People's Police,
Serving With Sincerity)

902
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:25,110
Relax a little, will you?

903
00:48:25,370 --> 00:48:27,110
You're so tense
you're going to give me indigestion.

904
00:48:27,180 --> 00:48:29,380
I'm sorry.
I heard this place is small...

905
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:31,010
but has a lot of incidents,

906
00:48:31,080 --> 00:48:34,720
- so I was a little on edge.
- Onjeong's not that these days.

907
00:48:35,320 --> 00:48:36,850
It's very peaceful.

908
00:48:38,320 --> 00:48:40,960
- Excuse me.
- Oh, Officer Jeong.

909
00:48:41,390 --> 00:48:43,860
Actually, I mean Detective Jeong.

910
00:48:44,830 --> 00:48:47,400
Hello, sir.
I've heard so much about you.

911
00:48:47,860 --> 00:48:50,800
I wonder what our chief
has been saying about me.

912
00:48:50,900 --> 00:48:53,770
No, I didn't say much.
Just that you started here,

913
00:48:53,840 --> 00:48:56,310
then got transferred
to the detective division,

914
00:48:56,410 --> 00:48:58,040
and got assigned
to the regional police agency,

915
00:48:58,110 --> 00:48:59,110
so we barely see you anymore.

916
00:49:01,780 --> 00:49:03,010
Is that really all he said?

917
00:49:04,550 --> 00:49:06,420
And that while you were here,

918
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:08,920
you met a nurse
as fierce as a tiger,

919
00:49:08,980 --> 00:49:11,120
and got married.

920
00:49:13,960 --> 00:49:15,020
Here comes the tiger, the tiger.

921
00:49:15,620 --> 00:49:16,630
What?

922
00:49:20,560 --> 00:49:23,570
- Have some sweet rice drink.
- Right, thanks.

923
00:49:25,500 --> 00:49:28,600
- What's this?
- Honey. It's just that...

924
00:49:28,770 --> 00:49:32,870
I mean, we barely see each other
once a month as it is,

925
00:49:33,280 --> 00:49:34,410
so if you're in Onjeong,

926
00:49:34,480 --> 00:49:36,850
you should see your wife first.
Why are you here?

927
00:49:37,010 --> 00:49:40,050
You know, I wonder why I did that.

928
00:49:41,020 --> 00:49:45,350
Our Detective Jeong is in the wrong.
Officer Kim, arrest him.

929
00:49:45,550 --> 00:49:48,460
- I'll arrest him for real.
- Chief.

930
00:49:48,520 --> 00:49:50,460
- Arrest him.
- No, I was on my way.

931
00:49:50,530 --> 00:49:52,930
- You, come here.
- Arrest him.

932
00:49:52,990 --> 00:49:56,530
I was on my way. Chief.

933
00:49:57,500 --> 00:50:00,270
Welcome to
all our new employees this year.

934
00:50:08,610 --> 00:50:10,380
Our company, Taehan Fashion,

935
00:50:10,610 --> 00:50:13,950
has achieved truly dazzling growth
over the past two years.

936
00:50:14,320 --> 00:50:16,690
From FG, which has solidified
its position in the overseas market,

937
00:50:17,520 --> 00:50:19,390
to Pelliv, which is now holding...

938
00:50:19,450 --> 00:50:21,620
its first fashion show
after expanding stores nationwide.

939
00:50:21,990 --> 00:50:26,290
All of this success is a miracle
created by your perfect teamwork.

940
00:50:26,760 --> 00:50:32,600
As we always have, let's continue
to aim higher together.

941
00:50:35,870 --> 00:50:38,070
And now, Director Pacu Nacho,

942
00:50:38,140 --> 00:50:41,340
who has worked so hard
for Taehan Fashion,

943
00:50:42,180 --> 00:50:44,380
will be transferring
to the food division,

944
00:50:44,450 --> 00:50:45,450
effective today.

945
00:50:49,620 --> 00:50:53,560
- All right.
- What? Why is everyone so happy?

946
00:50:53,920 --> 00:50:56,830
Well, it's because you always gave
the employees such a hard time.

947
00:50:58,160 --> 00:51:00,730
Does that mean
the director's position is now open?

948
00:51:00,830 --> 00:51:02,900
Not at all.
One of you will be appointed...

949
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:04,470
as the new managing director.

950
00:51:05,270 --> 00:51:06,470
Ms. Gong?

951
00:51:12,510 --> 00:51:14,780
- What the...
- Parachute hire!

952
00:51:15,980 --> 00:51:17,350
- Disappointed!
- Go away!

953
00:51:17,350 --> 00:51:19,750
Hey,
why is everyone so disappointed?

954
00:51:20,020 --> 00:51:22,620
Well, you took the position
after kicking my husband out.

955
00:51:22,720 --> 00:51:24,590
Did you really expect
to be loved for it?

956
00:51:27,890 --> 00:51:28,960
He's ugly.

957
00:51:29,520 --> 00:51:30,530
I'm not impressed.

958
00:51:39,070 --> 00:51:40,470
Does it make any sense
to make samples...

959
00:51:40,540 --> 00:51:41,770
without testing the fabric first?

960
00:51:42,040 --> 00:51:43,070
I'm sorry.

961
00:51:44,170 --> 00:51:45,340
Just get it done.

962
00:51:46,610 --> 00:51:50,180
Gosh, why has Kim So Hye become
so angry lately? It's scary.

963
00:51:50,810 --> 00:51:52,980
What do you mean? It's sexy.

964
00:51:54,880 --> 00:51:59,020
- What?
- You didn't know? They're dating.

965
00:51:59,150 --> 00:52:00,920
What? Since when?

966
00:52:01,460 --> 00:52:03,290
They say Ms. Kim got drunk,

967
00:52:03,360 --> 00:52:05,890
went over to Mr. Jo's place,
and kissed him.

968
00:52:09,400 --> 00:52:12,930
I've really learned so much
from you, Ms. Gong.

969
00:52:18,940 --> 00:52:21,180
She only learned the bad things
from me, didn't she?

970
00:52:22,340 --> 00:52:25,810
This won't do. I think we need
to change our team's name.

971
00:52:26,380 --> 00:52:27,580
To the Romance Team.

972
00:52:30,090 --> 00:52:31,090
I'm so lonely.

973
00:52:33,820 --> 00:52:36,060
What? Are they a couple already?
They're new employees.

974
00:52:36,790 --> 00:52:37,830
Unbelievable.

975
00:52:38,860 --> 00:52:41,130
- They didn't even test it.
- Calm down, honey.

976
00:52:42,600 --> 00:52:43,870
There are couples everywhere.

977
00:52:46,270 --> 00:52:48,870
It's delicious, right?
Sundae, Korean sausage.

978
00:52:54,310 --> 00:52:55,340
Excuse me, Director.

979
00:52:56,110 --> 00:52:58,950
You shouldn't be slacking off
like this on your very first day.

980
00:52:59,080 --> 00:53:02,850
Hey, I'm not slacking off.
I'm people-watching, you see?

981
00:53:02,950 --> 00:53:05,020
I have to see what
foods consumers respond to...

982
00:53:05,090 --> 00:53:06,390
and what flavors
they're interested in.

983
00:53:06,390 --> 00:53:08,690
I have to see it for myself, right?

984
00:53:09,690 --> 00:53:12,360
Do you think doing this will improve
our declining sales?

985
00:53:13,190 --> 00:53:14,360
Do you not know who I am?

986
00:53:14,860 --> 00:53:17,570
I'm known for my trend-setting
brand awareness...

987
00:53:17,630 --> 00:53:19,200
and my original marketing...

988
00:53:19,270 --> 00:53:23,240
- Brand Director Yang Pacu Nacho.
- Right.

989
00:53:24,510 --> 00:53:26,610
Come on. Let's go
beyond the Republic of Korea...

990
00:53:26,680 --> 00:53:28,680
and conquer the palates
of the entire world.

991
00:53:28,810 --> 00:53:30,350
Vamos!

992
00:53:33,620 --> 00:53:34,820
Yes, I understand.

993
00:53:35,350 --> 00:53:36,990
We at Labellin are also grateful...

994
00:53:37,050 --> 00:53:39,720
you featured our actress Yoon Seo
so beautifully. Yes.

995
00:53:40,790 --> 00:53:43,290
The next feature photo shoot?

996
00:53:44,690 --> 00:53:48,130
I'm very grateful for the offer,

997
00:53:48,200 --> 00:53:51,000
but my schedule is a little tight
right now. Yes.

998
00:53:51,670 --> 00:53:55,900
I'll check my schedule for next week
and get back to you then. Yes.

999
00:53:56,300 --> 00:53:59,140
Yes, thank you. Yes.

1000
00:54:01,310 --> 00:54:02,410
Okay.

1001
00:54:05,110 --> 00:54:06,380
Next outfit.

1002
00:54:08,020 --> 00:54:10,490
- Let's steam them one more time.
- Yes, ma'am.

1003
00:54:13,760 --> 00:54:14,960
Yes, I was just...

1004
00:54:28,340 --> 00:54:29,540
We're taking him
to the operating room now.

1005
00:54:30,710 --> 00:54:33,110
- Could you contact the doctor?
- Yes.

1006
00:54:35,640 --> 00:54:37,250
(Emergency Medical Center)

1007
00:54:42,520 --> 00:54:45,020
- Hold still.
- Be a little gentler.

1008
00:54:46,390 --> 00:54:49,060
Do you keep getting hurt
because you miss me?

1009
00:54:50,360 --> 00:54:51,660
Excuse me, Dr. Gong.

1010
00:54:51,730 --> 00:54:54,260
Your ego is getting terminal,
you know?

1011
00:54:54,330 --> 00:54:55,330
Just treat me.

1012
00:54:59,200 --> 00:55:01,600
Hey,
aren't you careful when you walk?

1013
00:55:01,900 --> 00:55:03,570
Why do you keep coming in
with the same injury?

1014
00:55:04,010 --> 00:55:05,010
Let go.

1015
00:55:07,680 --> 00:55:10,380
Are you crazy?
What if someone sees us?

1016
00:55:10,880 --> 00:55:12,150
Why? So what if they do?

1017
00:55:12,610 --> 00:55:13,920
It's only a secret relationship
at home.

1018
00:55:14,020 --> 00:55:15,620
Everyone at the hospital
knows I have a girlfriend.

1019
00:55:15,880 --> 00:55:19,650
Still. You must be crazy.

1020
00:55:19,990 --> 00:55:21,090
Hey, are you okay?

1021
00:55:21,960 --> 00:55:22,960
Hello.

1022
00:55:23,860 --> 00:55:26,760
It's a real honor to meet you both.

1023
00:55:27,400 --> 00:55:31,370
Your recently published book,
"Across 30 Years of Night"...

1024
00:55:31,430 --> 00:55:33,270
has become a bestseller.

1025
00:55:33,270 --> 00:55:35,170
I'd like to ask your thoughts
on that.

1026
00:55:37,940 --> 00:55:38,940
Well...

1027
00:55:39,510 --> 00:55:41,280
I had nowhere to send it,

1028
00:55:41,910 --> 00:55:43,480
and I couldn't throw it away...

1029
00:55:44,850 --> 00:55:48,120
This personal diary that I
just couldn't part with...

1030
00:55:48,980 --> 00:55:51,920
found its rightful owner
after 30 years.

1031
00:55:52,120 --> 00:55:54,490
And to hear
it has brought great comfort...

1032
00:55:54,560 --> 00:55:57,730
to so many people,
I'm just incredibly grateful.

1033
00:55:58,330 --> 00:56:02,460
Yes, the format
of the book is quite unique.

1034
00:56:02,760 --> 00:56:05,930
On the left pages are
the wife's faded diary entries...

1035
00:56:06,000 --> 00:56:07,070
from 30 years ago.

1036
00:56:07,300 --> 00:56:10,000
And on the right pages
are the husband's replies...

1037
00:56:10,070 --> 00:56:12,940
after his return.
The two are facing each other.

1038
00:56:13,210 --> 00:56:16,950
Is there a particular reason
you chose this alternating format?

1039
00:56:19,650 --> 00:56:21,380
For 30 years,

1040
00:56:21,850 --> 00:56:25,290
my wife thought
she was living those years alone.

1041
00:56:26,790 --> 00:56:29,160
I wanted to turn them
into years we spent together.

1042
00:56:30,390 --> 00:56:34,060
So your love finally connected
across 30 years.

1043
00:56:34,530 --> 00:56:38,800
Perhaps that's why it has touched
the hearts of so many readers.

1044
00:56:42,970 --> 00:56:45,170
What?
You want to introduce kiosks...

1045
00:56:45,240 --> 00:56:47,440
and a smart ordering system
to the market?

1046
00:56:48,310 --> 00:56:49,410
All right, look.

1047
00:56:49,810 --> 00:56:52,010
To bring in people in their 20s
and 30s,

1048
00:56:52,280 --> 00:56:55,520
we need to improve accessibility.
Okay?

1049
00:56:55,580 --> 00:56:57,620
I get the idea,

1050
00:56:57,990 --> 00:57:00,760
but what about the older vendors?
How will they adjust?

1051
00:57:00,820 --> 00:57:02,890
We just need to actively provide
training and support.

1052
00:57:03,730 --> 00:57:04,830
Hey, Gong Jeong Han.

1053
00:57:05,160 --> 00:57:07,360
Why do you have to fight me
on everything?

1054
00:57:07,630 --> 00:57:11,330
Fight you? Hey, I'm the Chairman.

1055
00:57:11,430 --> 00:57:14,700
Oh, whatever will I do?
I'm a city councilman.

1056
00:57:15,370 --> 00:57:17,810
- It keeps getting worse. What?
- Jeong Han.

1057
00:57:18,140 --> 00:57:20,380
Oh, you're here too. Hey, guys.

1058
00:57:20,680 --> 00:57:22,940
- Did you see the news article?
- What?

1059
00:57:23,010 --> 00:57:24,080
What article?

1060
00:57:24,080 --> 00:57:25,380
A corruption scandal involving...

1061
00:57:25,380 --> 00:57:27,850
Councilor Hwang
and Mayor Jang Tae Sik broke out...

1062
00:57:27,850 --> 00:57:29,180
and he was ousted.

1063
00:57:29,520 --> 00:57:30,520
- What?
- Really?

1064
00:57:32,350 --> 00:57:34,090
That's no way
for a politician to behave.

1065
00:57:34,890 --> 00:57:36,390
There were rumors
about it for a while.

1066
00:57:36,490 --> 00:57:37,690
I guess it was bound to happen.

1067
00:57:37,790 --> 00:57:41,560
Man, you're missing the point. Look.

1068
00:57:41,630 --> 00:57:44,700
The mayor's office is vacant now.

1069
00:57:47,200 --> 00:57:49,440
Hey, Dong Ik, you...

1070
00:57:50,210 --> 00:57:52,570
You should run for mayor of Onjeong.

1071
00:57:54,140 --> 00:57:55,910
But I can't be mayor...

1072
00:57:55,910 --> 00:57:57,410
and a Korean medicine doctor
at the same time.

1073
00:57:57,810 --> 00:57:58,880
What are you worried about?

1074
00:57:59,180 --> 00:58:01,380
Your father
can take over the clinic, can't he?

1075
00:58:01,420 --> 00:58:03,650
Right. My father?

1076
00:58:04,890 --> 00:58:06,220
Would he come back?

1077
00:58:19,030 --> 00:58:20,030
Oh, my.

1078
00:58:20,740 --> 00:58:22,270
Thank you so much, Mr. Yang.

1079
00:58:23,300 --> 00:58:27,810
There are no clinics or hospitals
nearby, so this is a lifesaver.

1080
00:58:29,080 --> 00:58:31,780
- How much is it?
- Don't worry about the fee.

1081
00:58:32,550 --> 00:58:35,080
Section Chief Jeong,
how old are you this year?

1082
00:58:35,880 --> 00:58:38,490
I'm turning 60 this year.
Why do you ask?

1083
00:58:38,650 --> 00:58:42,720
If you have children
or acquaintances under 40,

1084
00:58:43,220 --> 00:58:45,490
please have them go
to a Blood Donation Center...

1085
00:58:45,560 --> 00:58:47,930
and register to donate
hematopoietic stem cells.

1086
00:58:48,900 --> 00:58:50,330
Is that all I need to do?

1087
00:58:50,700 --> 00:58:53,200
It's not an easy decision to make.

1088
00:58:54,100 --> 00:58:57,310
But it's a precious act
that saves lives.

1089
00:58:57,770 --> 00:58:59,240
After all,
a donation saved my life, too.

1090
00:59:00,710 --> 00:59:01,710
I see.

1091
00:59:07,320 --> 00:59:09,680
Councilor Yang,
why are you calling again?

1092
00:59:11,590 --> 00:59:13,150
I told you I'm not going back.

1093
00:59:15,860 --> 00:59:17,290
Hey, Yang Seon Chul.

1094
00:59:19,390 --> 00:59:21,300
Hey, it's good to see you,
my friend.

1095
00:59:21,760 --> 00:59:22,900
Good to see you, Gi Cheol.

1096
00:59:23,830 --> 00:59:26,600
- Are you doing okay?
- Yes, I'm fit as a fiddle.

1097
00:59:27,000 --> 00:59:29,970
You know, you never came back
no matter how many times we called,

1098
00:59:30,040 --> 00:59:31,840
just drifting like the wind
and clouds,

1099
00:59:31,910 --> 00:59:34,210
roaming the country
with just an acupuncture kit.

1100
00:59:34,680 --> 00:59:36,740
And now
that your son is running for mayor,

1101
00:59:37,210 --> 00:59:39,350
you finally show up? You rascal.

1102
00:59:40,420 --> 00:59:41,480
That's how it turned out.

1103
00:59:41,920 --> 00:59:43,020
It's good you're back.

1104
00:59:44,390 --> 00:59:45,390
Hey.

1105
00:59:46,390 --> 00:59:47,720
But really, are you okay?

1106
00:59:49,160 --> 00:59:51,590
It's wonderful
that your father-in-law is back.

1107
00:59:51,660 --> 00:59:53,730
Right? For our Ji Ah's
first birthday photos,

1108
00:59:53,800 --> 00:59:56,700
we can all be in them together.
If Father was the only one missing,

1109
00:59:56,760 --> 00:59:58,370
it would have been awkward
taking a family photo.

1110
00:59:58,570 --> 01:00:00,400
Oh, then they should go
home to see Father.

1111
01:00:00,400 --> 01:00:02,670
- Why did they come here?
- Come on, why?

1112
01:00:02,740 --> 01:00:04,270
Father will be staying at home
from now on anyway.

1113
01:00:04,340 --> 01:00:07,010
Besides,
today isn't just any day, is it?

1114
01:00:07,140 --> 01:00:08,140
It's the day...

1115
01:00:08,210 --> 01:00:09,910
our Dr. Han makes her comeback
on the show.

1116
01:00:11,880 --> 01:00:12,880
But...

1117
01:00:13,450 --> 01:00:14,680
why does your skin look so dull?

1118
01:00:15,380 --> 01:00:18,750
Why is your skin so dull?
Did you not sleep well? Hold on.

1119
01:00:20,860 --> 01:00:23,490
We need to do this to bring
some color to your face.

1120
01:00:23,560 --> 01:00:25,360
That way you'll look good on camera.

1121
01:00:25,390 --> 01:00:28,600
- No.
- Hold on. We need to do a massage.

1122
01:00:28,660 --> 01:00:30,600
- Here, like this.
- No.

1123
01:00:30,730 --> 01:00:32,530
- Like this.
- That hurts.

1124
01:00:33,130 --> 01:00:34,940
- You have to massage it like this.
- Seriously.

1125
01:00:36,400 --> 01:00:40,240
This is a bit too flashy, so I'll go
with the clean look we had before.

1126
01:00:40,510 --> 01:00:43,580
Wow, Yang Eun Bin.

1127
01:00:44,450 --> 01:00:46,880
Thank you for being in charge
of our Dr. Han's styling.

1128
01:00:47,350 --> 01:00:50,890
The honor is all mine, thank you.
I'll do my best, Dr. Han.

1129
01:00:51,020 --> 01:00:52,650
And you too, Manager Cha.

1130
01:00:54,920 --> 01:00:57,260
It's been so long. I'm so nervous.

1131
01:00:57,790 --> 01:01:00,860
Really? Okay, look at me.
Take a deep breath.

1132
01:01:05,330 --> 01:01:06,430
One more time.

1133
01:01:12,840 --> 01:01:15,240
Oh my, honey, I thought you said
you couldn't come.

1134
01:01:15,680 --> 01:01:19,750
You're still so naive.
It was a joke.

1135
01:01:20,950 --> 01:01:24,520
Ta-da, surprise.

1136
01:01:25,850 --> 01:01:26,890
Thank you.

1137
01:01:28,620 --> 01:01:30,860
- We came too.
- Come on in.

1138
01:01:30,930 --> 01:01:31,930
- Oh my.
- Hello.

1139
01:01:32,260 --> 01:01:34,900
What's this?
I thought you were all busy.

1140
01:01:35,030 --> 01:01:37,300
You're making your comeback
after two years.

1141
01:01:37,370 --> 01:01:41,040
Of course we had to be here. Ta-da.

1142
01:01:41,100 --> 01:01:42,600
(Your son-in-law Hyun Bin,
your number one fan for life)

1143
01:01:42,770 --> 01:01:45,140
- What is this?
- What is that?

1144
01:01:48,380 --> 01:01:49,780
Seong Mi must be nervous.

1145
01:01:49,840 --> 01:01:52,550
How long has it been
since her last live show?

1146
01:01:52,750 --> 01:01:54,080
Well, her cheering squad is there.

1147
01:01:54,150 --> 01:01:55,720
She will get a boost of energy.

1148
01:01:55,780 --> 01:01:57,790
Yes, but where's our Ji Ah?

1149
01:01:58,220 --> 01:02:00,120
Ji Hu took her outside.

1150
01:02:00,290 --> 01:02:03,930
- A trial marriage and childcare.
- Really.

1151
01:02:04,560 --> 01:02:07,460
Do you think our Ji Hu
will marry his first love too?

1152
01:02:08,060 --> 01:02:12,430
Are you nervous
about seeing your first love on TV?

1153
01:02:12,770 --> 01:02:13,840
What are you talking about?

1154
01:02:14,670 --> 01:02:16,670
My first love is Se Ri.

1155
01:02:20,040 --> 01:02:21,340
We still have some time
before the broadcast,

1156
01:02:21,410 --> 01:02:23,850
- so let's eat first.
- Yes, enjoy your meal.

1157
01:02:24,510 --> 01:02:25,510
Okay.

1158
01:02:26,480 --> 01:02:30,450
(Recipe For Love)

1159
01:02:31,550 --> 01:02:32,690
Just a moment.

1160
01:02:33,390 --> 01:02:36,060
Be careful this doesn't
get messed up.

1161
01:02:36,690 --> 01:02:37,690
Thank you.

1162
01:02:42,830 --> 01:02:44,270
You've got this.

1163
01:02:44,570 --> 01:02:46,330
- You got this.
- You can do it.

1164
01:02:48,740 --> 01:02:50,070
You can do it.

1165
01:02:50,140 --> 01:02:53,240
(Recipe For Love)

1166
01:02:53,310 --> 01:02:56,440
Okay, we're starting now.
Three, two, one, and cue.

1167
01:02:57,580 --> 01:02:58,650
Hello, everyone.

1168
01:02:59,180 --> 01:03:01,850
I'm Han Seong Mi,
and I'm here to give your family...

1169
01:03:01,920 --> 01:03:02,980
the recipe for love.

1170
01:03:06,590 --> 01:03:08,620
(You are my recipe for love.)

1171
01:03:08,690 --> 01:03:10,260
(Congratulations on your comeback)

1172
01:03:10,320 --> 01:03:12,760
Yes, it's so good to see you
again looking so healthy.

1173
01:03:12,830 --> 01:03:14,530
It's so wonderful to have you back,
Dr. Han.

1174
01:03:14,630 --> 01:03:15,700
Thank you.

1175
01:03:16,200 --> 01:03:20,270
You spent the last two years
fighting an illness.

1176
01:03:20,570 --> 01:03:22,570
What was your mindset
during that time?

1177
01:03:23,970 --> 01:03:27,440
To be honest,
what got me through that time...

1178
01:03:27,780 --> 01:03:29,510
wasn't some grand miracle.

1179
01:03:30,340 --> 01:03:31,810
It was the love of my family...

1180
01:03:32,280 --> 01:03:34,020
who never left my side.

1181
01:03:35,980 --> 01:03:39,450
And that time wasn't a battle
against my illness.

1182
01:03:40,520 --> 01:03:41,790
It was a time in my life...

1183
01:03:42,360 --> 01:03:45,630
when I feel I received
the greatest love.

1184
01:03:46,990 --> 01:03:49,560
Because our families are
the ones closest to us,

1185
01:03:50,260 --> 01:03:52,100
it's easier to have
misunderstandings,

1186
01:03:52,570 --> 01:03:54,500
and the hurt can go much deeper.

1187
01:03:55,570 --> 01:03:56,700
So today,

1188
01:03:56,970 --> 01:03:59,540
if you're crying
because of your family,

1189
01:04:00,040 --> 01:04:01,540
I want to give you
the courage to reach out.

1190
01:04:02,110 --> 01:04:05,810
If you're lonely, I want to give you
hope that you can be together.

1191
01:04:06,880 --> 01:04:09,980
And if you're exhausted
by your family,

1192
01:04:10,620 --> 01:04:12,750
I want to give you
the strength to love.

1193
01:04:14,190 --> 01:04:15,790
The family makeover show...

1194
01:04:15,860 --> 01:04:18,360
that prescribes love
for broken homes,

1195
01:04:18,790 --> 01:04:22,200
Han Seong Mi's Recipe For Love...

1196
01:04:23,100 --> 01:04:24,770
starts now.

1197
01:04:27,900 --> 01:04:29,000
- You're doing great!
- You're my prescription for love!

1198
01:04:29,000 --> 01:04:31,370
- Go, Han Seong Mi! Recipe For Love!
- Go, Dr. Han.

1199
01:04:40,210 --> 01:04:44,090
Okay, time for a picture. Everyone,
gather around. Come on, over here.

1200
01:04:44,790 --> 01:04:46,850
- Looks like that's everyone.
- Come on, over here.

1201
01:04:46,920 --> 01:04:48,520
Oh, sit over here.

1202
01:04:50,990 --> 01:04:53,590
Okay. Okay. Wait a minute.
But where's Yang Eun Bin?

1203
01:04:53,660 --> 01:04:54,660
Yang Eun Bin?

1204
01:04:55,400 --> 01:04:57,800
Oh, wait. Where did Woo Jae go?

1205
01:04:58,000 --> 01:04:59,330
What? Oh, Woo Jae.
He isn't here either.

1206
01:04:59,970 --> 01:05:01,370
- Seriously.
- Woo Jae.

1207
01:05:01,440 --> 01:05:02,570
That darn kid.

1208
01:05:03,640 --> 01:05:05,410
Honestly, he couldn't just wait.

1209
01:05:05,670 --> 01:05:07,480
- Hey.
- What?

1210
01:05:07,680 --> 01:05:10,080
- Hey.
- Please let us be together.

1211
01:05:10,140 --> 01:05:11,850
- What's all this?
- What? What's going on?

1212
01:05:11,910 --> 01:05:14,680
- I love Woo Jae.
- Be quiet.

1213
01:05:15,020 --> 01:05:16,250
- Woo Jae.
- Mom. Mom...

1214
01:05:16,320 --> 01:05:18,050
- I won't give you up.
- Mom.

1215
01:05:18,120 --> 01:05:19,120
What's happening? What is this?

1216
01:05:20,150 --> 01:05:21,790
- Sit down.
- Hey, hey.

1217
01:05:22,390 --> 01:05:23,890
Oh, these kids...

1218
01:05:25,090 --> 01:05:26,190
You little brat.

1219
01:05:27,800 --> 01:05:29,260
Okay, smile, everyone.

1220
01:05:33,870 --> 01:05:35,270
Just smile for now.

1221
01:05:35,840 --> 01:05:37,270
You're in for it when we get home.

1222
01:05:46,510 --> 01:05:48,950
(Special thanks to Eom Ji In
for her appearance)

1223
01:06:09,940 --> 01:06:12,810
(Recipe For Love)

1224
01:06:12,870 --> 01:06:14,980
- Get over here.
- Hey, Bucket.

1225
01:06:15,040 --> 01:06:17,180
- Get over here.
- Please, don't do this.

1226
01:06:18,480 --> 01:06:19,480
NG.

1227
01:06:20,980 --> 01:06:22,980
- Who was it? Who did it?
- You pushed me?

1228
01:06:23,050 --> 01:06:26,250
I did it. I'm sorry.
Dae Han is scarier than Jeong Han.

1229
01:06:27,460 --> 01:06:29,560
- It's okay. All right.
- Ready, go.

1230
01:06:34,300 --> 01:06:38,970
- Dong Ik!
- Cut. Okay.

1231
01:06:45,610 --> 01:06:48,510
- A winter swim is the best.
- A winter swim.

1232
01:06:50,510 --> 01:06:51,850
I'm sorry.

1233
01:06:54,250 --> 01:06:55,880
Great, let's continue.

1234
01:07:09,100 --> 01:07:10,970
I think we got everything.

1235
01:07:13,330 --> 01:07:15,870
(Thank you to everyone
who has loved Recipe For Love.)
